Data visualisation with Matplotlib |  Seaborn | PlotlyExpress

Matplotlib is used for small and low level plot elements. Matplotlib is not informative as seaborn and plotlyexpress.

import matplotlib.pyplot  as plt 
plt.plot(x,y)
plt.show()

Seaborn is used for creating statistical plots with less code and it is built on MatPlotlib library.

impot seaborn as sns
sns.histoplot(df["col"], kde=True)

PlotlyExpress is used for creating interactive charts and has easy syntax compared to two other libraries.

import plotly.express as px
px.scatter(df, x="col1", y="col2", color="category")
